article.headline: Thomas, Campbell lead Geo. Mason over William & Mary
article.linkText: Thomas, Campbell lead Geo. Mason over William & Mary
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Will Thomas scored 19 points on 8-for-10 shooting and Folarin Campbell added 17 to lead George Mason to a 76-63 win over William & Mary on Tuesday. George Mason (10-7, 4-3 Colonial Athletic Association) never trailed, grabbing an early lead on a 3-pointer by Jordan Carter, who scored 12 points on 4-for-5 shooting. John Vaughan added 12 for the Patriots. George Mason outshot William & Mary 53.8 percent to 48.9 percent from the field, though the Tribe (10-7, 3-4) outrebounded the Patriots 29-24. Laimis Kisielius led the Tribe with 17 points, and Nathan Mann scored 13.
